sols_latex:
We see from the hint that the formula for an inverse of $2\times{2}$
matrices of the form

\begin{align*}
A=
\begin{bmatrix}
a  &  b\\
c  &  d
\end{bmatrix}
\end{align*}

is

\begin{align*}
A^{-1}=\frac{1}{\text{det}(A)}\begin{bmatrix}
d  &  -b\\
-c  &  a
\end{bmatrix}.
\end{align*}

In this example we have

\begin{align*}
A=\begin{bmatrix}
1  &  2\\
1  &  1
\end{bmatrix}
\end{align*}

and so

\begin{align*}
\displaystyle{}\text{det}(A)=1-2=-1.
\end{align*}

Therefore we have that

\begin{align*}
A^{-1}=-1
\begin{bmatrix}
1  &  -2\\
-1  &  1
\end{bmatrix}
=
\begin{bmatrix}
-1  &  2\\
1  &  -1
\end{bmatrix}.
\end{align*}

